import seaborn as sns
import pandas as pd
import matplotlib.pyplot as plt

def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    sns.histplot(data=data, x='group_size', kde=False, color='blue')
    plt.axvline(x=data['group_size'].mean(), color='red', linestyle='--', label=f'Mean: {data["group_size"].mean():.2f}')
    plt.axvline(x=data['group_size'].median(), color='green', linestyle='--', label=f'Median: {data["group_size"].median():.2f}')
    plt.legend()
    plt.title('What is the distribution of group sizes?', wrap=True)
    plt.xlabel('Group Size')
    plt.ylabel('Frequency')
    return plt

chart = plot(data)
```

import seaborn as sns
import pandas as pd
import matplotlib.pyplot as plt

def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    sns.set(style="whitegrid")
    ax = sns.barplot(x="group", y="group_size", data=data, palette="Blues_d")
    ax.axhline(y=data['group_size'].mean(), color='r', linestyle='--', label='Mean Group Size: {:.2f}'.format(data['group_size'].mean()))
    ax.legend(loc='upper right')
    plt.title('What is the average group size?', wrap=True)
    return plt

chart = plot(data)
```

import seaborn as sns
import pandas as pd
import matplotlib.pyplot as plt

def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    sns.countplot(x='group', data=data, palette='Blues')
    plt.title('What is the distribution of people across groups?', wrap=True)
    plt.xlabel('Group')
    plt.ylabel('Count of People')
    return plt

chart = plot(data)

```
import seaborn as sns
import pandas as pd
import matplotlib.pyplot as plt

def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    group_sizes = data.groupby('group_size').size().reset_index(name='counts')
    fig, ax = plt.subplots(figsize=(6, 6))
    ax.pie(group_sizes['counts'], labels=group_sizes['group_size'], autopct='%1.1f%%', startangle=90)
    ax.axis('equal')
    ax.set_title('What are the most common group sizes?')
    return plt

chart = plot(data)
```

import seaborn as sns
import pandas as pd
import matplotlib.pyplot as plt

def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    group_counts = data.groupby('group')['person'].nunique().reset_index()
    sns.barplot(x='group', y='person', data=group_counts, palette='Blues_d')
    plt.title('What are the most common group compositions?', wrap=True)
    plt.xlabel('Group ID')
    plt.ylabel('Count of unique people')
    return plt

chart = plot(data)
